A command to create a test repository

Command creates repos with arbitrary commits for testing.

  git-add-to /tmp/foobar.git init

destructively creates /tmp/foobar.git with the initial commit of a README.

  git-add-to foobar.git {0..9}

adds commits {0..9}

After the command completes, there is also a clone of the repo
in the current, working directory to facilitate further work.

Add a test line.
